    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "makes sense. so basically even if the government says they're regulating it for \"safety\" or \"misinformation,\" it's still a violation of the contract because they're messing with individual liberty. do u think there's any way a government could actually justify regulating the internet without breaking that contract, or is any regulation inherently a breach?",
